data.title: Profile: Miranda Norris
data.meta_description: Journalists news from the Witney Gazette
data.text:
Latest articles from Miranda Norris

Public notices: Oktoberfest, hostel demolition and Rhodes House

Public notices are adverts placed by councils and other local authorities to inform people of developments in their areas.

Road bridge closed for second time 'cutting off residents from rest of city'

A road bridge in Oxford has been closed to traffic for the second time in eight months effectively cutting off residents from the rest of the city.

Pet charity questions greyhound stadium over data on injuries and deaths

Pet charity The Blue Cross has written to Oxford Greyhound Stadium asking them to reveal the number of injuries and deaths of greyhounds at the track.

Fire service dealing with 'high number of calls' of dogs left in hot cars

Oxfordshire Fire Service has warned pet owners as temperatures soar after they received "a high number of calls involving dogs being left in hot cars".

'Body' on railway tracks turns out to be doll

A 'body' spotted near railway tracks that caused all lines between between Oxford and Swindon to be blocked turned out to be a mannequin.

Staff shake-up as council moves to take back control of services

Some 270 employees are set to move from working for a company owned by three district councils to West Oxfordshire District Council alone by the end of the year.

Image released after a man exposed himself to person in street

Police have released a CCTV image of a person they want to trace after a man exposed himself to a member of the public in the street.

Swan loses life partner following 'entirely avoidable' dog attack

A swan has lost its lifelong partner after it was set upon by a dog at an Oxfordshire lake.

Hospital 'swept sexual harassment complaint' against surgeon 'under carpet'

A female trainee’s complaint to Oxford hospital bosses of sexual harassment by a transplant surgeon was “swiftly swept under the carpet” a decade ago.
